  "prompt": "What is it like to live in Darjeeling?",
  "response": "Living in Darjeeling, located in the state of West Bengal, India, offers a unique experience characterized by:\n\n1. Climate and Geography\n- Cool mountain climate\n- Situated in the Himalayan foothills\n- Scenic views of mountains and tea gardens\n- Elevation around 6,700 feet above sea level\n\n2. Culture\n- Diverse population including Nepali, Tibetan, and Bengali communities\n- Rich cultural heritage\n- Multilingual environment\n- Blend of different traditions and customs\n\n3. Economy\n- Tourism is a major economic driver\n- Tea production is significant\n- Many people work in hospitality, tourism, and tea plantations\n- Limited job opportunities compared to larger cities\n\n4. Lifestyle\n- Peaceful and relaxed mountain town atmosphere\n- Strong sense of community\n- Limited urban amenities\n- Good walkability\n- Rich in natural beauty\n\n5. Challenges\n- Relatively isolated location\n- Limited infrastructure\n- Occasional landslides during monsoon season\n- Potential transportation difficulties\n- Some economic limitations\n\n6. Attractions\n- Famous for Darjeeling tea\n- Historic toy train (UNESCO World Heritage Site)\n- Buddhist monasteries\n- Stunning mountain landscapes\n- Close proximity to natural attractions\n\nOverall, Darjeeling offers a serene, culturally rich mountain living experience with beautiful surroundings.",
